cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.SC, cs.NA 

The paper presents algorithms for discrete transforms, which are commonly used in signal processing and data compression. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of computer science that deal with these topics. Specifically, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a likely category as the paper presents new algorithms for computing discrete transforms. cs.IT (Information Theory) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the numerical accuracy of the algorithms. cs.SI (Signal Processing) and cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) are also possible categories as the paper deals with signal processing and computation of transforms. Finally, cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a possible category as the paper discusses the reduction of arithmetic operations in the algorithms.
